  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "It now states: \"We use the content you provide to improve our services, such as to train the models that run our services.",
    "Read our instructions on how to opt out of the use of your content to train our models\" (OpenAI, 2023).",
    "However, consent is only a valid basis for prompts containing personal information about the user themselves.",
    "If users generate prompts that include personal data from other persons, they cannot validly consent on their behalf (Novelli et al., 2024).",
    "When a generative model is capable of producing output which includes personal data, the issue of how training data was collected remains relevant throughout its life cycle."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "If users generate prompts that include personal data from other persons, they cannot validly consent on their behalf (Novelli et al., 2024)."
  ]
}